@startuml
title PayMate Project: Waterfall Model Application

skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #ADD8E6
    BorderColor #4682B4
    ArrowColor #333
    FontName Inter
    FontSize 14
}
skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #F5F5F5
    BorderColor #888
    FontName Inter
    FontSize 12
}
skinparam partition {
    BackgroundColor #EFEFEF
    BorderColor #A9A9A9
    FontName Inter
    FontSize 16
    FontColor #333
}

start

partition "1. Requirements Analysis" {
    :Gather and Document All Requirements;
    note right
        - **Define all features upfront:**
          Login, Signup, User Profile.
        - **Detail every payment flow:**
          UPI, Bank Transfer, QR Scan.
        - **Specify all Bill Payment categories.**
        - **Script the entire AI Chatbot dialogue.**
        - **Output:** A comprehensive Software
          Requirement Specification (SRS) document.
    end note
}

->

partition "2. System Design" {
    :Create System & UI/UX Design;
    note right
        - **Create finalized wireframes and mockups**
          for every single screen (Dashboard, Transfer, etc.).
        - **Design the complete system architecture**
          and database schema.
        - **Policy:** No changes are allowed after
          this phase is complete.
    end note
}

->

partition "3. Implementation" {
    :Code the Full Application;
    note right
        - **Build the entire frontend** in Next.js.
        - **Develop the complete backend API.**
        - **Integrate with all payment gateways**
          (Stripe, PayPal, Razorpay) as per the design.
        - **Code the Genkit AI flows** based on the
          scripted dialogues.
    end note
}

->

partition "4. Testing" {
    :Perform Quality Assurance;
    note right
        - **The full application is tested only after**
          all coding is complete.
        - **Bugs found here are difficult and costly to fix**
          as they may require going back to the design phase,
          which is discouraged by the model.
    end note
}

->

partition "5. Deployment" {
    :Release to Production;
    note right
        - **The completed application is deployed**
          to the production server (e.g., Firebase App Hosting).
        - **The final product is released** to end-users.
    end note
}

->

partition "6. Maintenance" {
    :Provide Ongoing Support;
    note right
        - **Handle post-launch support** and bug fixes.
        - **Any new features or major changes** would
          require starting a brand new waterfall cycle,
          beginning with requirements analysis.
    end note
}

stop
@enduml
